You hold up your Ace until the third round, discovering that spades were 5-3.  There are eight tricks on top and you must aim to develop a ninth from the minor suits without allowing LHO (the danger hand) to gain the lead.|
pg| ***** 9 ***** |


---------------------------------------------------------------------------
nt|^z@3^c@2^^|n^|5|
Lg|b|
at|^bAns
Looking for a 3-3 break in the club suit can wait.  The first priority is to seek an extra trick from the diamonds.  If the suit breaks 3-3, you will gain two extra tricks.  Life will also be easier when RHO holds four diamonds, since you can concede a fourth round of the suit to the safe hand.  The difficult situation is where LHO holds four diamonds.  In that case you must aim to duck a diamond trick into RHO's hand.  Suppose you lead the ten diamonds with the intention of running the card to RHO.  LHO will foil that temporarily by covering with the Jack.|
pg| ***** 10 ***** |


