nt|^z@3^c@2^^|n^|5|
Lg|b|
at|^bAns
You win the trick in dummy and return to your hand with the King of clubs.  You then lead the 4 of diamonds towards the dummy.  LHO cannot afford to rise with the 8 or you will make all five diamond tricks.  He therefore plays low and you cover with dummy’s 7, ducking the trick into the safe hand.  RHO wins with the 9 and the contract is yours.  You will win RHO's return and score four diamond tricks to go with your five top winners in the other suits.  It’s a pretty good one and will succeed against four diamonds with LHO unless he has an unbeatable J98x.|
